The past few years have been filled with many unknowns and big life questions for all of us, myself included. I’m beginning to see some new stepping stones along my path, and have been carving out a creative home for myself over at @_duendecollective.🕊️

While I will continue to share vintage objects and furniture pieces, I’m also bringing together my interests and passions in a new way, with a focus on ritual, intention, meaning and connection. Lighting incense when I get out of bed is a favorite daily ritual of mine, so I’m thrilled that Duende’s first custom offering is a hand-sculpted ceramic incense holder, made by my incredibly gifted friend @finea_studio. Each piece is unique, molded by hand from a sensory textured stoneware in two colorways.

I’m grateful for this shifting lens and fresh perspective — sometimes the smallest tweak helps to uncover what was there all along. Sending you lots of love and warmth this holiday season.

A few years ago, my friend @finea_studio gifted me a handmade ceramic soap dish with a playful face. I loved it so much that to this day, I’ve used it as a spoon rest in my kitchen. As my @_duen_de project evolved, I knew I wanted to focus on special tools, resources and objects to encourage ritual and moments away from a screen. I reached out to Rebekka about collaborating on an incense holder — an evolution of her original dish, now in a more raw, textured clay updated with eyes that hold sticks and a raised mouth to perfectly position an incense cone.

Every morning I drink my coffee cuddled on the couch with my dog, a stick of oud incense burning in the holder my dear friend lovingly created. I cherish these early moments of the day so so much.

The Finea x Duende incense holders are available in two colorways through Duende’s website, or in person at our first stockist (!) @fruitshairlab in Nashville. Please reach out if you’re interested in carrying a handful in your shop.
